    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 5 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER ES62-5A, ES62-5D, ES67-5A AND
        ES67-5D - TROUBLESHOOTING - TROUBLESHOOTING CHART
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>TROUBLESHOOTING CHART</title>
        <table id="t1301001" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Troubleshooting Chart</title>
            <tgroup cols="3" align="center" charoff="50" char="c">
                <colspec colname="1" colwidth="1.00in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" colwidth="2.49in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" colwidth="2.97in"/>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" morerows="0" rotate="0">
                            <para>Condition</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" morerows="0" rotate="0">
                            <para>Possible Causes</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" morerows="0" rotate="0">
                            <para>Remedy</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" morerows="0" rotate="0">
                            <para>Noise in</para>
                            <para id="x1301004">Neutral</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" morerows="0" rotate="0">
                            <seqlist style="arabic">
                                <item>
                                    <para>Misalignment of transmission.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Worn flywheel pilot bearing.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Worn or scored countershaft.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Sprung or worn countershaft.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Excessive backlash in gears.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Scuffed gear tooth contact surface.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Insufficient lubrication.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Use of incorrect grade of lubricant.</para>
                                </item>
                            </seqlist>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" morerows="0" rotate="0">
                            <seqlist style="arabic">
                                <item>
                                    <para>Tighten transmission to flywheel housing mounting bolts. Check bell housing
                                        pilot to flywheel housing pilot for burrs, wear or damage. Repair or replace as
                                        required.
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Replace pilot bearing.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Replace countershaft. Use correct lube and fill level. Refer to GROUP 10 -
                                        LUBRICATION in the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual.
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Adjust with shims. Refer to
                                        <xref refid="x1301002"/>
                                        <hotlnk document="s13010_19.xml" xrefid="x1301002">REASSEMBLY, CASE</hotlnk>.
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Replace gear. Refer to GROUP 10 - LUBRICATION in the CTS-5000 Master Service
                                        Manual.
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Fill to fill level hole.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Refer to GROUP 10 - LUBRICATION in the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual.</para>
                                </item>
                            </seqlist>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" morerows="0" rotate="0">
                            <para>Noise in Gear</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" morerows="0" rotate="0">
                            <seqlist style="arabic">
                                <item>
                                    <para>Rough, chipped, or tapered sliding gear teeth.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Noisy speedometer gears.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Excessive end play of countershaft gears.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Refer to conditions listed under
                                        <xref refid="x1301004"/>"Noise in Neutral."
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                            </seqlist>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" morerows="0" rotate="0">
                            <seqlist style="arabic">
                                <item>
                                    <para>Replace defective gears.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Check driven gear sleeve, bushing and gears for wear. Replace as required.
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Adjust with shims. Refer to
                                        <xref refid="x1301002"/>
                                        <hotlnk document="s13010_19.xml" xrefid="x1301002">REASSEMBLY, CASE</hotlnk>.
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Refer to remedies listed under
                                        <xref refid="x1301004"/>"Noise in Neutral."
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                            </seqlist>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" morerows="0" rotate="0">
                            <para>Oil Leaks</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" morerows="0" rotate="0">
                            <seqlist style="arabic">
                                <item>
                                    <para>Oil level too high.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Wrong lubricant in unit.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Seals defective, wrong type or omitted from bearing cap.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Transmission breather omitted or plugged internally.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Screws loose, omitted or missing from shift tower, bearing caps, PTO, or
                                        covers.
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Oil drain-back openings in bearing caps or case plugged with varnish or
                                        dirt.
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Gasket shifted or squeezed out of position, broken gasket with pieces under
                                        the shift tower.
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Cracks or holes in castings.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Loose drain plug.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Oil leakage from engine.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Loose speedometer adapter or connections.</para>
                                </item>
                            </seqlist>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" morerows="0" rotate="0">
                            <seqlist style="arabic">
                                <item>
                                    <para>Drain excess oil to level of fill hole.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Refer to GROUP 10 - LUBRICATION in the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Replace seals with correct part number. Refer to MT513 Parts Catalog.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Replace breather with correct part number. Refer to MT513 Parts Catalog.
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Replace missing screws or tighten to correct value. Refer to the
                                        <xref refid="t1301004"/>
                                        <hotlnk document="s13010_32.xml" xrefid="t1301004">TORQUE CHART</hotlnk>.
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Clean bearing cap and case to remove obstruction.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Clean mating surfaces and replace gasket.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Replace casting.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Tighten to eliminate leak.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Locate source and repair.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Tighten or replace adapter and connections.</para>
                                </item>
                            </seqlist>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" morerows="0" rotate="0">
                            <para>Walking or Jumping Out of Gear</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" morerows="0" rotate="0">
                            <seqlist style="arabic">
                                <item>
                                    <para>External interference, such as floorboard opening, preventing full
                                        engagement.
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>An internal malfunction, such as worn clutching teeth, allowing transmission
                                        to shift out of position.
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Use of heavy shift lever extensions.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Broken shift rail poppet springs.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Worn shift rail poppet notches.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Bent or sprung shift rails.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Excessive end play in drive gear or countershaft, caused by worn bearings or
                                        retainers.
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Worn or missing thrust rings.</para>
                                </item>
                            </seqlist>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" morerows="0" rotate="0">
                            <seqlist style="arabic">
                                <item>
                                    <para>Locate interference and eliminate to allow full engagement.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Replace gear and collar. Verify good clutch release and correct if required.
                                        Instruct driver on proper shift technique.
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Correct lever to manufacturer's specification.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Replace springs.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Replace rail.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Replace rail. Instruct driver on proper shift technique.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Replace bearings and retainer as required. Reset end play. Refer to
                                        <xref refid="x1301002"/>
                                        <hotlnk document="s13010_19.xml" xrefid="x1301002">REASSEMBLY, CASE</hotlnk>.
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Replace thrust rings.</para>
                                </item>
                            </seqlist>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" morerows="0" rotate="0">
                            <para>Hard Shifting</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" morerows="0" rotate="0">
                            <seqlist style="arabic">
                                <item>
                                    <para>Lack of lubricant or wrong lubricant used, causing buildup of sticky varnish
                                        and sludge deposits on splines of shaft and gears.
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Badly worn or bent shift forks.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Sliding clutch gears tight on splines of shaft.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Clutch teeth burred over, chipped or badly broken because of improper
                                        shifting.
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Binding or interference of shift lever with other objects or rods inside the
                                        cab.
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Clutch dragging.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Free running gears seized or galled on either the thrust face or diameters.
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                            </seqlist>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" morerows="0" rotate="0">
                            <seqlist style="arabic">
                                <item>
                                    <para>Clean splines and gears. Refill with correct lube and fill level. Refer to
                                        GROUP 10 - LUBRICATION in the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual.
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Replace shift forks. Instruct driver on proper shift technique.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Check splines and gears for wear or defects. Replace as required.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Replace clutch gear. Instruct driver on proper shift technique.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Locate and eliminate interference.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Refer to GROUP 11 - CLUTCH in the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual. If drag
                                        problem cannot be eliminated, replace clutch.
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Replace parts as required. Refer to GROUP 10 - LUBRICATION in the CTS-5000
                                        Master Service Manual.
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                            </seqlist>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" morerows="0" rotate="0">
                            <para>Sticking in Gear</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" morerows="0" rotate="0">
                            <seqlist style="arabic">
                                <item>
                                    <para>Clutch not releasing.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Sliding clutch gears tight on splines.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Chips wedged between or under splines of shaft and gear.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Excessive wear or lost motion in shifter tower.</para>
                                </item>
                            </seqlist>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" morerows="0" rotate="0">
                            <seqlist style="arabic">
                                <item>
                                    <para>Adjust clutch. Refer to GROUP 11 - CLUTCH in the CTS-5000 Master Service
                                        Manual. If problem cannot be eliminated, replace clutch.
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Check splines for wear or defects and replace as required.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Clean parts and check for wear. Replace as required.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Replace worn parts.</para>
                                </item>
                            </seqlist>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" morerows="0" rotate="0">
                            <para>Bearing Failures</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" morerows="0" rotate="0">
                            <seqlist style="arabic">
                                <item>
                                    <para>Fatigue of raceways or balls.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Wrong type or grade of lubricant.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Lack of lubricant.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Broken retainers, brinelled races and fretting caused by vibration.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Bearings set up too tight or too loose.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Improper installation resulting in brinelled bearings.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Improper fit of shafts or bore.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Acid etching due to water in lube.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Vehicle overload.</para>
                                </item>
                            </seqlist>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3" morerows="0" rotate="0">
                            <seqlist style="arabic">
                                <item>
                                    <para>Replace bearing.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Replace bearing. Refer to GROUP 10 - LUBRICATION in the CTS-5000 Master
                                        Service Manual.
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Replace failed bearings. Determine source of vibration and correct
                                        condition.
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Refer to
                                        <xref refid="x1301002"/>
                                        <hotlnk document="s13010_19.xml" xrefid="x1301002">REASSEMBLY, CASE</hotlnk>
                                        for shimming specifications.
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Refer to
                                        <xref refid="x1301002"/>
                                        <hotlnk document="s13010_19.xml" xrefid="x1301002">REASSEMBLY, CASE</hotlnk>.
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Replace as required.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Drain and flush transmission. Replace bearings. Fill with correct lube. Refer
                                        to GROUP 10 - LUBRICATION in the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual.
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Replace bearings. Restrict vehicle usage to design capacity.</para>
                                </item>
                            </seqlist>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
